"Um, god I have so much I wanna say to you

I had this whole thing memorized and I'm just blanking right now

Ah.. you know me, I think about love a lot. I think about relationships a lot. And I think when it comes to relationships I've been a very... scared and selfish man. I've been self indulgent for a long time thinking that, like, love peaks at the beginning and inevitably it fades because of time and circumstances and fights and things, and because of this mindset, it made me start to think that relationships are impossible to last. And I always thought, "marriages, like, who would do that? Doesn't make any sense." You know, it means giving up freedoms and diluting desires and cutting off this big pursuit for like finding the highest peak.

Then.. with you, and over the last... just my whole life, just different relationships, and all this time, forgiveness, and your patience, the lessons i've learned that that was just really juvenile way of thinking, that marriage isn't about losing out on things. Marriage is about unlocking your heart and your mind to an entirely different dimension of emotions.

Hahaha... it's pretty good, about right? You know I like analogies.

And so while I have climbed different peaks of love. There's an entire mountain range left to be explored that I have no idea even exists, and you and I have already been through so much, especially this past year. And you've taught me so much about myself. You make me less scared of the future. This really scared man, you've made me a lot less scared. And I wanna keep exploring you.

And that's why I wanted to meet you here, in your childhood home -- in your backyard that you used to play, that you used to play in -- and just your world expanded, right? This used to be your world, this used to be the boundaries of everything you knew. But just like your world expanded, just like you turned into a beautiful, smart, worldly loving person, I think our relationship can blossom in the same way. And I want to start that next journey in the same place that that little girl first did, if you allow me.

So, Helen? I want to marry you.

I want to marry you.


This is a nice view from here, I should have done this a while ago.

Helen, will you... will you marry me?

I love you so much.

I love you.

Take em off. I think I'm supposed to -- I should have watched a YouTube video for this.

(I think it's the left side!) Left side, left side! Yeah, left side, left side!

(Oh my god it's beautiful, baby.. It's so beautiful), aww, it fits.


(Ohh my god, ohh my god)"
